Dto == Data Transfer Object

In Kotlin, the invoke operator is a special function that can be defined in a class,
allowing instances of that class to be called as if they were functions

di = Dependency Injection: Helps to make our dependencies replaceable so we can use @Inject in our classes instead of
hardcoding the dependencies

:: creates a member reference or a class reference.

->

separates the parameters and body of a lambda expression.

separates the parameters and return type declaration in a function type.

separates the condition and body of a when expression branch.

